Katharine Butler, of Dorchester, the daughter of retired Foreign Office diplomat Sir Michael Butler, grew up in Mapperton.

She said: ‘This beautiful landscape is now threatened to become a hideous industrial park of glass and steel. It is effectively the industrialisation of the countryside. These farms have to be in the right places.

‘If Richard Drax is so keen on renewable energy why not put the farm in view of his beautiful home, within the high walls of Charborough Park and not have to disturb others?

‘It’s hard not to feel that the impetus behind this scheme is financial and not about renewable energy. It will receive a huge sum in subsidies on top of the electricity that is generated that will be sold to the national grid.’

