‘The local area will benefit from a community fund to be established. At the end of the project the land will return to the existing agricultural use.’

Good Energy said the solar farm will have a capacity to generate 28MW of power and will generate enough renewable electricity to power around 6,800 homes.

Ben Gowers, head of development at Good Energy said: ‘We would like to thank everyone who has supported the project so far.

‘The location and design of the solar farm will make the most of the area’s sunshine for renewable energy generation while minimising impacts on the landscape, and enhancing biodiversity.’

The scheme is expected to begin generating electricity as early as April next year.

